            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I spent four years at this school until 2012, where I completed the 10th grade. Unfortunately, my experience there was marred by pervasive racism and demeaning attitudes from fellow students. Moreover, many of the teachers displayed favoritism. My English teacher, Aprajita Tomar, dissuaded me from pursuing a science track after the 10th grade, unaware of my grades in science and math. I went on to earn a master's degree in applied computer science, and today, I work as a software developer in Canada.\n\nThe sports teacher was unfair in training students and prioritized those recommended by their parents. The school culture was often divisive, with many students not even acknowledging each other. Regardless of one's abilities, I felt that I didn't receive the necessary support one expects from an educational institution, which I believe wasted my time and hindered my growth as a student and an individual. It's been more than 10 years now, and I can only hope and wish the school is a better place. If you currently study there, don't let that place get to you. Believe in yourself, don't be shy, and don't let anyone tell you what you can or cannot do.",
          "publisher": {
